    <div class="services__details__text">
        <p>Hair transplantation is a minimally invasive surgical procedure used to treat permanent hair loss. Healthy hair follicles are taken from a donor area (usually the back or sides of the scalp) and implanted into thinning or bald areas. The transplanted hair grows naturally and permanently.</p>
            <div class="blog__details__text">
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 1 - 1. Consultation & Planning</h5>
                        <p>A detailed scalp and hair density evaluation is performed to understand hair loss patterns. Based on facial proportions, a natural hairline is designed and the required graft count and technique are finalized.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 2 - Donar Area Preparation</h5>
                        <p>The donor area is trimmed, cleaned, and prepared under sterile conditions. Local anesthesia is administered to ensure a comfortable and pain-free procedure.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 3 - Graft extraction</h5>
                        <p>Healthy hair follicles are carefully extracted using advanced techniques such as FUE or FUT. The grafts are preserved in a controlled solution to maintain their strength and survival.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 4 - Recipient Area Preparation</h5>
                        <p>Tiny channels are created in the treatment area with precise angles and direction. This step ensures natural hair growth and a realistic appearance.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 5 - Graft implantation</h5>
                        <p>The harvested follicles are implanted carefully into the prepared sites. Hair density and pattern are customized to blend seamlessly with existing hair.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog__details__text__item">
                        <h5>Step 6 - Post-Procedure Care</h5>
                        <p>Patients are discharged on the same day with minimal downtime. Temporary redness or swelling may occur, and detailed aftercare instructions are provided.</p>
                    </div>
